- Hashed locally → much lower entropy than whole-genome data.
- Familial matching probability drops orders of magnitude (10,000x as noted), limiting GEDmatch-style exposure.
- Parents/siblings/children share fewer predictable patterns in non-coding repeats.

This feeds the public announcement’s `dna_root_hash` (now a STR-derived commitment) and XRPL deterministic seeds. Raw full DNA stays air-gapped on local NVMe. Only STR hashes enter proofs or low-trust anchors. This protects collateral family exposure while still binding the UUID `bd6e1085-9450-485a-a30a-0bb68669c75b`, eSIM `89033023426309010000054675483625`, and SN512A device fingerprint (`system_state`).

